{"questionId":"35031519","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A hollow chocolate box is manufactured in the form of a right prism with a regular hexagonal&nbsp;base. The height of the prism is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo> </mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math>,&nbsp;and the top and base of the prism have sides of&nbsp;length <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/41786dc03655ee03fe531aa4e3a4f7d702dd2b4b.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Sketch the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>300</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math>, for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>16</mn></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/2f99cad888f4c814ea6a07b4e44dcaf01c18e339.png\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>A1A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <strong><em>A1</em></strong> for correct shape, <strong><em>A1</em></strong> for roots in correct place with some indication of scale (indicated by a labelled point).</p>\n<p><br><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"35031519","referenceCode":"21M.2.SL.TZ2.5c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Sketch the graph of V=3003x-94x3, for 0≤x≤16.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.3—Graphing"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}